txt.en: You have rescued the wounded Elf
One of the Malledhrim has been wounded, and fallen behind enemy lines. While the valiant warrior can still move, he can fight only weakly and requires your aid to escape from enemy territory.
'I should be able to make it the rest of the way from here. My thanks [placeholder].'
'I'll keep up as best I can.'

'You have come to help? I have tried to avoid the Orcs for as long as I can, but I cannot move swiftly.\n\n'If you can give me a hand, we may be able to fight our way out of here! I fear, though, that I will be of little help, for I am weak.'
Aid the fallen Malledhrim warrior in his escape from the war-torn fortifications of Gathbúrz, back towards Thangúlhad.

'One of our wounded companions made his way back here earlier, claiming that an unfamiliar [placeholder] helped him escape from great peril.\n\n'I believe we have you to thank for this, [placeholder]? Well done. Every warrior you save will stand by our side when we strive against the darkness ahead.'
Handelen is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\n\nYou should inform Handelen of the aid you lent to the wounded Elf-warrior.
'Quickly, let us be away before they find us!'
Escort the wounded Elf to safety
